    q: "Can you leave an outdoor sauna out in winter?",
    a: "Yes - that is what they are built for, and the cold makes the post-sauna plunge far better. A quality shell in thermowood or clear cedar handles freeze-thaw well, and both electric and wood heaters work fine in the cold. Expect a slightly longer heat-up, keep snow off the roof and vents, and make sure any electrical run and GFCI protection are rated for outdoor use.",
